// Out-of-scope exemplar supplement, 2026-05-27.
//
// Targets the parking-pass hallucination bug found in R10 retest:
//   oos2_parking_pass → kNN classified as 'location_directions' (low margin,
//   tied with other intents), so OOS REFUSE tier didn't fire and the agent
//   answered from search_kb chunks that mentioned parking in passing.
//
// Adds 12 paraphrased non-library university questions that students
// commonly ask but are NOT library-handled. None are verbatim copies of
// the test cases (no test-set leakage). All represent the kind of "is
// this our job?" boundary the bot must hold cleanly.
//
// None of these have library-specific keywords, so they should not
// inappropriately catch valid library questions like "do you have a
// book about parking?" (that would still classify as find_resource).

// parking
{"intent": "out_of_scope", "utterance": "How do I buy a parking pass?", "source": "manual_2026-05-27_oos"}
{"intent": "out_of_scope", "utterance": "Where do I get a parking permit?", "source": "manual_2026-05-27_oos"}
{"intent": "out_of_scope", "utterance": "Is there visitor parking on campus?", "source": "manual_2026-05-27_oos"}

